---
title: "Services — Slade Networks"
description: "UniFi installation and ongoing support for homes and small businesses — Wi-Fi, cameras, VoIP, cabling, and more. Serving the Finger Lakes region in upstate NY."
navActive: services
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .section { padding: 24px 0 56px }
    .supportSection { padding: 0 0 56px }

    /* Primary service cards */
    .primaryGrid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 16px;
    }

    .primaryCard {
      background: var(--white);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      border-radius: var(--r-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
      padding: 24px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      transition: transform .3s var(--ease), box-shadow .3s var(--ease), border-color .3s var(--ease);
    }
    .primaryCard:hover {
      transform: translateY(-3px);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
      border-color: var(--primary-100);
    }

    .primaryCard h3 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: var(--gray-900);
    }

    .primaryCard p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-500);
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.65;
      flex: 1;
    }

    .primaryCard .media {
      margin-top: 20px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 80px;
    }

    .primaryCard .media img {
      width: 55%;
      max-width: 200px;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
      object-fit: contain;
      transition: transform .3s var(--ease);
    }

    .primaryCard:hover .media img {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    /* Divider */
    .divider {
      border: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      margin: 36px 0 28px;
    }

    /* Secondary service cards */
    .secondaryGrid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 14px;
    }

    .secondaryCard {
      background: var(--white);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      border-radius: var(--r-lg);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xs);
      padding: 20px;
      transition: transform .3s var(--ease), box-shadow .3s var(--ease), border-color .3s var(--ease);
    }
    .secondaryCard:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
      border-color: var(--primary-100);
    }

    .secondaryCard h3 {
      margin: 0 0 6px;
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      color: var(--gray-900);
    }

    .secondaryCard p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-500);
      font-size: 13.5px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    /* Pricing note */
    .pricingNote {
      margin-top: 24px;
      padding: 18px 22px;
      background: var(--gray-50);
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
      border-radius: var(--r-lg);
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--gray-500);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .pricingNote strong { color: var(--gray-900) }
    .pricingNote a { color: var(--primary); font-weight: 600 }

    /* Support card */
    .supportCard {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(37,99,235,.03) 0%, rgba(37,99,235,.06) 100%);
      border: 1px solid var(--primary-200);
      border-radius: var(--r-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
      padding: 32px;
    }

    .supportBadge {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      background: var(--primary-100);
      color: var(--primary);
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: .07em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      border-radius: var(--r-sm);
      padding: 5px 10px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .supportCard h2 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      font-size: 22px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    .supportCard > p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--gray-500);
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.65;
      max-width: 82ch;
    }
    .supportCard > p + p { margin-top: 10px }

    .supportFooter {
      margin-top: 22px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 16px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .supportFooter .processLink {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--primary);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .ctaSection { padding: 0 0 72px }

    @media(max-width:980px) {
      .primaryGrid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr }
      .secondaryGrid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr }
    }
    @media(max-width:700px) {
      .primaryGrid { grid-template-columns: 1fr }
    }
    @media(max-width:480px) {
      .secondaryGrid { grid-template-columns: 1fr }
    }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M12 1v4m0 14v4M4.22 4.22l2.83 2.83m9.9 9.9 2.83 2.83M1 12h4m14 0h4M4.22 19.78l2.83-2.83m9.9-9.9 2.83-2.83"/></svg>
          Full-service installs
        </div>
        <h1>Services</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          UniFi installation and ongoing support for homes and small businesses — from the hardware to the handoff, with continued support when you need it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="sectionLabel">Core services</p>
        <div class="primaryGrid reveal-stagger">

          <article class="primaryCard">
            <h3>Wi-Fi</h3>
            <p>Planned AP placement, clean installation, and coverage verified where you actually use it — living areas, offices, outdoor spaces. No dead spots, no guessing.</p>
            <div class="media">
              <img src="/assets/u7-pro-xg-2.png" alt="UniFi Wi-Fi access point">
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="primaryCard">
            <h3>Cameras</h3>
            <p>Good angles, no blind spots, and footage you can access from your phone. We choose placement, avoid gaps in coverage, and confirm remote viewing works before we leave.</p>
            <div class="media">
              <img src="/assets/uvc-g6-pro-turret-10.png" alt="UniFi camera">
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="primaryCard">
            <h3>VoIP Phones</h3>
            <p>Business calling on UniFi Talk — clean cutover, number porting handled, and tested end-to-end. Calls don't drop, phones just work.</p>
            <div class="media">
              <img src="/assets/utp-g3-touch-enterprise-1.png" alt="UniFi Talk phone">
            </div>
          </article>

        </div>

        <hr class="divider">

        <p class="sectionLabel">Supporting work</p>
        <div class="secondaryGrid reveal-stagger">

          <article class="secondaryCard">
            <h3>Structured cabling</h3>
            <p>Neat Ethernet runs, labeled jacks, and clean wall plates — easy to trace when you add something later.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="secondaryCard">
            <h3>Gateways and switching</h3>
            <p>Right-sized core gear, cleanly installed for stable performance as devices are added over time.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="secondaryCard">
            <h3>Racks and mounting</h3>
            <p>Equipment mounted and patched properly — labeled ports, organized cables, easy to service.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="secondaryCard">
            <h3>Power and failover</h3>
            <p>Battery backup for critical gear, and cellular failover so a downed connection doesn't take everything offline.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="secondaryCard">
            <h3>Network storage</h3>
            <p>Centralized files and camera recordings — accessible to the right people, backed up.</p>
          </article>

          <article class="secondaryCard">
            <h3>Display and casting</h3>
            <p>Digital signage and casting setups that stay connected and are easy to update without babysitting.</p>
          </article>

        </div>

        <div class="pricingNote reveal">
          <strong>Transparent pricing.</strong> Every job starts with a free on-site consultation and a written, itemized quote before any work begins — no vague estimates, no surprise add-ons at the end. <a href="/process/">See how the process works &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="supportSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="supportCard">
          <div class="supportBadge">Recommended add-on</div>
          <h2>Ongoing Support Plan</h2>
          <p>Most problems that come up after install don't need a site visit — they need someone who knows the system and can fix it fast. We monitor your network, handle firmware updates before they cause issues, and troubleshoot remotely so you're not dealing with it yourself.</p>
          <p>Especially useful for businesses where downtime costs real money.</p>
          <ul class="benefitList" aria-label="Support plan benefits">
            <li>Remote monitoring</li>
            <li>Firmware updates handled</li>
            <li>Remote troubleshooting</li>
            <li>Priority response</li>
            <li>Most issues fixed without a site visit</li>
            <li>One point of contact for anything network</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="supportFooter">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Ask about support plans</a>
            <a class="processLink" href="/process/">How the full process works &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Start with a free consultation</h2>
            <p>We come to you, walk the space, and put together a written quote — no commitment required.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Request a free consultation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
